Aws Regions:
    is present all around the world
    is a cluster of Data centers
    Names can be Asia Pacific (Mumbai) (ap-south-1), Australia (Sydney) ap-southeast-2,....
    Most of the AWS services are region-scoped
    Each region has many availability zones (2 to 6) usually 3

AWS Availability Zones:
    Names can be ap-southeast-2a, ap-southeast-2b, ap-southeast-2c
    Each availability zone (AZ) is one/more data centers with enough power, networking and connectivity
    They are separate and isolated from disasters
    They are still connected with one another with high bandwidth, ultra low-latency-network
    